jobs_results.title: Senior Android Engineer
jobs_results.description:
About Us

At AscentCore, we believe that great software starts with great people. Our strength comes from combining top-tier development practices with deep, meaningful relationships — both with our clients and our team. Even as we grow, we stay true to the values that define us: quality, speed, value, and innovation. These values help us build trust, not just in the technology we create, but in the way we work together.

We’re not just about hiring talent — we’re about fostering a community of individuals who are passionate, collaborative, and forward-thinking. We’re proud of our diverse expertise that spans multiple industries, giving us the ability to help companies not only transform but truly thrive.

At AscentCore, you’re part of something bigger. Whether we’re working on cutting-edge AI solutions or the next breakthrough in software, our mission is simple: to create technology that shapes the future, while building a community where everyone can grow and succeed together.

About the Role

For our partner, a leader in the audio entertainment industry with 150+ million users, we are looking for a Senior Android Engineer.

We have an established team at AscentCore working on next-gen features for the infotainment sector of our partner’s business, connecting users to numerous features that make driving a more pleasurable experience through the awesome content shared by the company: music, news and podcast streaming, among others.

This role is open in locations where we'd like to expand our local communities: Cluj-Napoca, Timisoara, Iasi.

Responsibilities
• Design, develop, test, and deploy Android-based solutions using common standards and frameworks
• Deliver products to market by working closely with customers, engineering, design, and program management teams in an Agile environment
• Analyse and/or contribute to software architecture
• Perform code reviews
• Write comprehensive documentation, making it easier for others to understand the code and the architecture decisions, facilitating smoother collaboration

Requirements
• Native Android development experience of 5+ years
• Proficient with Android Java and related Android development tools/technologies
• Android Automotive OS is a must
• Familiar with JNI practices
• AOSP development is nice to have
• Understanding of object-oriented design (OOD) and object-oriented programming (OOP)
• Familiarity with MVVM design patterns
• Knowledge of VAST/VPAID standards is a plus
• Experience with streaming technologies is a plus
• Commitment to “internal client” and customer service principles
• Ability to pay attention to details and be organized
• Ability to handle multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment
• Good English communication skills both written and verbal

Tech stack
• Android Java
• Dagger
• RxJava
• MVVM
• Git/Github
• Jenkins
• Agile Scrum/Kanban

Soft Skills
• Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to connect, collaborate, and work effectively with team members and stakeholders across all levels of the organization
• Skilled at guiding junior developers and sharing best practices, both in coding and in problem-solving approaches
• Take the initiative to propose new features, optimizations, or research areas that could benefit the team and the product, contributing to a culture of continuous improvement and growth.

Benefits
• Medical Benefits Package: Regina Maria
• Well-being: Access to 7Card App that offers a wide network of fitness and wellness facilities
• Flexible Benefits Program: Customizable options such as meal vouchers, private pensions, cultural vouchers, vacation vouchers, extra medical services, and sports or transport reimbursement
• Support for Certifications and Professional Development
• Rewards & Recognition programs
• Access to technical training, workshops, conferences, and other professional events
• Hybrid Work Schedule: A mix of flexibility and in-person collaboration
• Special Life Milestone Gifts: Celebrating major life events like weddings or the birth of a child
• Up to 26 vacation days, plus a day off for your birthday
• Participation in internal events: team buildings, holiday parties, picnics, and social gatherings
• Snacks and meals with the team
• Full coverage for business trips

Application Process

Submit Your Application: Once you’ve submitted your resume and any additional materials, our team will promptly review your application.

Initial Review: Within 1-2 weeks, you’ll hear back from us about next steps, which may include a request for more information or an interview invitation.

Interviews: You’ll meet with our technical panel to discuss your expertise and problem-solving skills.

You’ll also connect with your potential hiring manager to explore role-specific responsibilities and team dynamics.

In some cases, you may also have the opportunity to meet with the client.

Timeline: The entire process typically lasts between 1 to 3 weeks, depending on your availability and coordination with relevant stakeholders.

Feedback & Decision: After completing the interview process, we will provide feedback and inform you of the outcome.

jobs_results.title: Pitesti - Software Developers (Android, Embedded sau Server)
jobs_results.description:
Job description

TekGPS Engineering SRL este o companie din grupul Textron Specialized Vehicles, specializată în dezvoltarea de sisteme de management pentru vehicule electrice utilizate pe terenuri de agrement, în special pe terenuri de golf. Produsele noastre oferă clienților o interfață multimedia avansată pentru a îmbunătăți experiența de golf.

Textron Specialized Vehicles Inc. este un producător global de top al carturilor de golf, vehiculelor utilitare și de transport personal, snowmobilelor, vehiculelor off-road (side-by-sides), ATV-urilor, echipamentelor profesionale pentru întreținerea gazonului și echipamentelor de suport la sol. Textron Specialized Vehicles comercializează produse sub mai multe mărci diferite. Vehiculele sale pot fi găsite în diverse medii, de la terenuri de golf, fabrici, aeroporturi și comunități rezidențiale, până la parcuri tematice și rezervații de vânătoare.

Despre job

Pentru a ne desfășura activitatea la cele mai înalte standarde, lucrăm exclusiv de la birou. În acest moment, opțiunea de a lucra de acasă nu este disponibilă.

Locație: Pitești, România

Calificări necesare:

· Studii: Studenți, Absolvenți

· Nivel carieră: Începător (0-2 ani), Intermediar (2-5 ani), Avansat (>5 ani)

· Tip job: Full-time, Part-time

· Engleză: Nivel intermediar scris și vorbit

Căutăm în prezent Programatori și Testeri pentru roluri de software și hardware. Activitatea se desfășoară la sediul companiei. Avem 5 departamente: Android, Server, Embedded, Testare și Hardware. În funcție de aspirațiile și obiectivele tale viitoare, iată cerințele departamentelor pentru Software Development:

Software Developers:

Responsabilități:
• Dezvoltarea, traducerea și scrierea de cod pentru soluții software noi și existente, respectând specificațiile, inclusiv pentru interfețe de utilizator, baze de date și servicii back-end.
• Proiectarea, execuția și monitorizarea UnitTestelor pentru performanță și pentru Regression cu scopul identificării defectelor, izolarea zonelor ce necesită îmbunătățiri și depanare.
• Efectuarea analizei diagnostice a rezultatelor testelor și propunerea de soluții pentru problemele critice.
• Promovarea și diseminarea cunoștințelor privind cele mai bune practici în dezvoltarea aplicațiilor.
• Colaborarea cu echipe multifuncționale, incluzând administratori de rețea, analiști de sisteme, programatori și alți ingineri software, pentru a soluționa defectele în produse sau în sistemele companiei.

Cerințe (ce trebuie să știi sau să fii dispus să înveți):

· Android: Android Studio, Java/Kotlin, XML, Azure DevOps, GIT

· Server: C#, Entity Framework, MVC/ASP.NET, JavaScript, MSSQL Server, HTML/CSS, Knockout JS, Bootstrap, Leaflet JS, REST API, Microsoft SQL Server, Azure DevOps

· Embedded: C/C++, Visual Studio, GIT, Azure DevOps, sisteme embedded/RTOS, magistrale periferice (SPI, I2C, UART, CAN etc.)
• Puteti trimite CV-ul la adresa de email: gbalici@textron.com

jobs_results.title: Android Software Engineer
jobs_results.description:
About the role

We are looking for a talented Android Software Engineer eager to deliver a best-in-class mobile application. You will be directly involved in designing, developing, maintaining and enhancing the Fitbit Android application. You will be working alongside an international team of talented and dedicated colleagues who have a common goal to help people lead healthier lives. You will be responsible for proposing, evaluating and implementing software solutions that meet the need of the application. You will work with product managers, UI/UX designers, backend and frontend developers in order to create beautiful mobile user experiences that allow users to intuitively accomplish any task. Our mobile clients are a vital part of the user interface to the Fitbit platform.

Check out our current mobile app for Android at:
• https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.fitbit.FitbitMobile

Required Skills
• BS in Computer Science or equivalent work experience
• 4+ years experience in building mobile apps for Android
• Good knowledge and understanding of the Android SDK
• Object oriented software development experience with a solid grasp of algorithms and data structures
• Experience creating reusable components with elegant, intuitive API interfaces
• Experience working with databases and working with REST APIs
• Experience using a modern version control system
• Desire to work with design and product in order to define requirements
• Open minded about exploring and using new technologies
• A strong sense for when refactoring is needed
• Ability to work well in a team
• Excellent verbal and written communication skills
• Fluency in English is a must

Nice-to-have skills
• Experience in building hybrid apps: native and javascript based (PhoneGap, Cordova, Webviews) is a big plus
• Familiarity with Agile and Scrum methodologies
• A drive to keep performance high using profile guided optimization
• A feel for visual and interaction design
• A knack for appropriate abstraction
• Experience using Android NDK
• Experience collaborating with remote team members
• Experience working closely with product management to ship features in consumer oriented software
• Expertise in one or more of our core technology areas:
• Android UI / Graphics / Animation
• Bluetooth / Bluetooth Low Energy

jobs_results.title: Senior Android Developer - Freelance
Mobile Software Developer
jobs_results.description:
About Bitdefender

Bitdefender is a
cybersecurity leader delivering best-in-class threat prevention, detection, and
response solutions worldwide. Guardian over millions of consumer,
enterprise, and government environments, Bitdefender is one of the industry’s
most trusted experts for eliminating threats, protecting privacy, digital
identity and data, and enabling cyber resilience. With deep investments in
research and development, Bitdefender Labs discovers hundreds of new threats
each minute and validates billions of threat queries daily. The
company has pioneered breakthrough innovations in antimalware, IoT
security, behavioral analytics, and artificial intelligence and its technology
is licensed by more than 180 of the world’s most recognized technology brands.
Founded in 2001, Bitdefender has customers in 170+ countries with offices
around the world. For more information, visit https://www.bitdefender.com
About The Job

Bitdefender is a leader in security solutions and one of the best-known IT security brands.
We’re at the forefront of security innovation, and we’re looking for talented individuals to
shape the future of our products, our company, and the industry as a whole.

Our mobile apps are evolving to leverage cross-platform development using Flutter
to enhance our agility and efficiency. At the same time, we continue to rely on the
strength of native iOS development to ensure we deliver robust, secure, and
high-quality experiences for our users on iOS platform.

We are looking for a passionate Mobile Software Developer with expertise
in iOS development to join our team and help us take on exciting challenges
in security and mobile innovation.

What We’re Looking For

We’re seeking a creative and technology-driven individual with a solid programming background.
You should be eager to learn, solve complex problems, and work in an Agile environment to deliver
high-quality, high-performance mobile apps.

Ideally, You Should Have:
• 2+ years of iOS development experience, with expertise in Swift and iOS development tools (Xcode IDE, Instruments, Simulators).
• Solid understanding of iOS frameworks, Swift Packages, and dependency management tools like CocoaPods.
• Experience working with RESTful APIs to connect apps to back-end services.
• A strong grasp of the full mobile development lifecycle and experience with the Apple distribution process.
• The ability to write unit and functional tests to ensure code quality and coverage.
• Good knowledge of multithreaded programming and algorithmic thinking.
• Familiarity with Agile methodologies and version control systems (e.g., Git).
• Strong communication skills and fluency in English.

Bonus Points For:
• Experience with Flutter or other cross-platform development frameworks.
• A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or a related field.
• A portfolio of past projects (e.g., on GitHub, Bitbucket, or similar platforms).
• Knowledge of Android development or Kotlin.

What You’ll Do:
• Contribute to our mobile app evolution, supporting both the native iOS codebase and our transition to cross-platform development using Flutter.
• Collaborate with the team to develop and enhance existing iOS apps, ensuring high performance, security, and usability.
• Help design and build new features and applications to complement Bitdefender’s mobile ecosystem.
• Work with Product Owners, UX designers, QA engineers, and other developers in an Agile Scrum environment.
• Continuously evaluate and implement new tools, frameworks, and technologies to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of our development process.

What We Offer:
• A dynamic and exciting work environment in a leading cybersecurity company.
• Competitive benefits aligned with your performance and contribution.
• Opportunities for professional growth and involvement in cutting-edge projects.

RESPONSABILITIES
